ed agent with repo setup, concurrency gating, and timeout scaling.\\n    32→- All operations go through `RepoState` (`s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`) so they're logged to `console.log`.\\n    33→- Use the `entire` package for CLI interactions, not raw `exec.Command`.\\n    34→- Skip tests pending CLI fixes with `t.Skip(\\\"ENT-XXX: reason\\\")`.\\n    35→\\n    36→## Adding a New Agent\\n    37→\\n    38→1. Create `agents/<name>.go` implementing the `Agent` interface.\\n    39→2. Register it in `init()` with `Register(&YourAgent{})`.\\n    40→3. Add a `Bootstrap()` method for any CI-specific setup (auth config, warmup).\\n    41→4. Add a `RegisterGate(\\\"<name>\\\", N)` call if concurrency needs limiting.\\n    42→5. Ensure the agent name is accepted by `mise run test:e2e --agent <name>`.\\n    43→6. Add the agent to `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` matrix and `e2e-isolated.yml` options.\\n    44→\\n    45→## Environment Variables\\n    46→\\n    47→| Variable | Description | Default |\\n    48→|----------|-------------|---------|\\n    49→| `E2E_AGENT` | Agent to test (`claude-code`, `gemini-cli`, `opencode`, `factoryai-droid`, `kiro`) | all registered |\\n    50→| `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN` | Path to a pre-built `entire` binary | builds from source |\\n    51→| `E2E_TIMEOUT` | Timeout per prompt | `2m` |\\n    52→| `E2E_KEEP_REPOS` | Set to `1` to preserve temp repos after test | unset |\\n    53→| `E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR` | Override artifact output directory | `e2e/artifacts/<timestamp>` |\\n    54→| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Required for Claude Code | — |\\n    55→| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | Required for Gemini CLI | — |\\n    56→| `AMAZON_Q_SIGV4` | Enable headless IAM/SIGV4 auth for Kiro | unset |\\n    57→| `AWS_REGION` | AWS region for Kiro SIGV4 auth | `us-east-1` in CI |\\n    58→\\n    59→## Debugging Failures\\n    60→\\n    61→Artifacts are captured to `e2e/artifacts/` on every run (git-log, git-tree, console.log, checkpoint metadata, entire logs). Set `E2E_KEEP_REPOS=1` to preserve the temp repo — a symlink appears in the artifact dir pointing to it.\\n    62→\\n    63→Use the `debug-e2e` skill (`.claude/skills/debug-e2e/`) for a structured workflow when investigating failures.\\n    64→\\n    65→### Reading artifacts\\n    66→\\n    67→- `console.log` — full operation transcript including agent stdout/stderr\\n    68→- `git-log.txt` — commit history at time of failure\\n    69→- `git-tree.txt` — working tree state\\n    70→- `entire-logs/` — internal CLI logs\\n    71→\\n    72→### Fixing flaky tests\\n    73→\\n    74→When a test passes on retry but failed once, the problem is usually agent non-determinism, not a CLI bug. Common patterns:\\n    75→\\n    76→- **Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting**: The model output contains \\\"Does this look right?\\\" or \\\"Should I proceed?\\\". Fix: append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation, just make the change.\\\" to the prompt.\\n    77→- **Agent wrote to wrong path or created extra files**: Fix: be more explicit about exact file paths and what _not_ to do.\\n    78→- **Agent committed when it shouldn't have**: Fix: add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to the prompt.\\n    79→- **Checkpoint wait timeout**: `WaitForCheckpoint` or `WaitForCheckpointAdvanceFrom` exceeded deadline. Fix: increase the timeout argument.\\n    80→\\n    81→To diagnose: read `console.log` in the failing test's artifact directory. Compare what the agent actually did vs what the test expected.\\n    82→\\n    83→## CI Workflows\\n    84→\\n    85→- **`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`** — Runs full suite on push to main. Matrix: `[claude-code, opencode, gemini-cli, factoryai-droid, kiro]`.\\n    86→- **`.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml`** — Manual dispatch for debugging a single test. Inputs: agent + test name filter.\\n    87→\\n    88→Both workflows run `go run ./e2e/bootstrap` before tests to handle agent-specific CI setup (auth config, warmup).\\n    89→\\n    90→## Kiro Authentication\\n    91→\\n    92→Kiro E2E tests require the `kiro-cli-chat` binary (not `kiro-cli`). The desktop app wrapper (`kiro-cli`) ignores `AMAZON_Q_SIGV4` and always forces browser OAuth, which fails in headless environments.\\n    93→\\n    94→- **GitHub-hosted CI**: Workflows download `kiro-cli-chat` directly and use AWS OIDC credentials plus SIGV4 (`AMAZON_Q_SIGV4=1`).\\n    95→- **Local development**: Install `kiro-cli-chat` separately — the Kiro desktop app only provides `kiro-cli`. Download the standalone binary:\\n    96→  ```bash\\n    97→  KIRO_VERSION=\\\"1.27.0\\\"\\n    98→  curl -fsSL \\\"https://desktop-release.q.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/${KIRO_VERSION}/kirocli-$(uname -m)-$(uname -s | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]').zip\\\" -o kiro.zip\\n    99→  unzip -q kiro.zip && cp kirocli/bin/kiro-cli-chat ~/.local/bin/ && rm -rf kirocli kiro.zip\\n   100→  ```\\n   101→\\n   102→CI prerequisite: set `AWS_ROLE_ARN` repository secret so `aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials` can assume the role.\\n   103→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"6e6c2328-afd6-4740-992e-9c5eb60f4f58\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T22:00:40.883Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a42501637d37c0a1a\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_017R5GmJZJoV2EBd421aCSkM\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01Xd3hNhb8NQo9MUoyCu3Ukx\",\"uuid\":\"21716443-45f6-4bc7-bbad-74a220192b83\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T22:00:41.334Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"21716443-45f6-4bc7-bbad-74a220192b83\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"7682603d-1d7b-49cc-900b-ee77433e7db4\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"toasty-stargazing-mountain\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T22:00:41.389Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01Gjv6x2XzGCP6tzcHMBZWeD\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01DJcdZZg4BrEHrLeLDDKVhv\",\"name\":\"Grep\",\"